Diagram 2 (Correct Continuation)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par When black connects at 1, white 2 is a good move.
\par
\par If black tries to resist with 3, white 4 is a decisive blow!
\par
\par It is easy to see that black cannot live, even if the four white stones are captured.
\par
\par Instead of 3, even if black plays at 4, white captures the stone with \b\f1 A\b0\f0  and it becomes an eye vs. no eye capturing race.
\par }
